  <!-- S10 WHICH AMAZON ARE YOU COMPARING (6 subsections) -->
  <section id="species">
    <h2 class="cag-h2">Which Amazon Are You Actually Comparing?</h2>
    <p>This is the section no other page gives you. "Amazon" isn't one bird — it's a genus of more than thirty species, and the six most often set against a Grey vary as widely among themselves as any of them does from the Grey. A gentle Red-Lored and an operatic, hormonal Double-Yellow-Head are barely the same pet. Here's the honest head-to-head for each, using real photos. If you searched a specific matchup like African Grey vs Blue-Fronted Amazon or African Grey vs Yellow-Naped Amazon, start here.</p>
    {species.map((s) => (
      <article class="sp-block" id={s.id}>
        <div class="sp-media"><img src={s.img} width="640" height="480" alt={s.alt} loading="lazy"></div>
